#: ../source/notebooks/mmm/mmm_causal_identification.ipynb:10002
#: 3c3b2e9a1f70404cab88cff632bb6db7
msgid ""
"Introduction to Understanding Causal Relationships in Media Mix Modeling"
msgstr ""
"Introducción a la comprensión de las relaciones causales en el modelado de "
"mezcla de medios"

#: ../source/notebooks/mmm/mmm_causal_identification.ipynb:10004
#: d011d258685b42c5b013e6cd7a69721d
msgid ""
"Causal identification is about figuring out if we can prove a cause-and-"
"effect relationship using the data we have and our assumptions. This process"
" helps us establish clear links between different factors instead of looking"
" at their correlations. It is essential when working with observational "
"data, which can be affected by hidden factors and biases that make it hard "
"to see true causal relationships."
msgstr ""
"La identificación causal consiste en determinar si podemos probar una "
"relación de causa y efecto utilizando los datos que tenemos y nuestras "
"suposiciones. Este proceso nos ayuda a establecer vínculos claros entre "
"diferentes factores en lugar de centrarnos en sus correlaciones. Es esencial"
" al trabajar con datos observacionales, que pueden verse afectados por "
"factores ocultos y sesgos que dificultan la identificación de verdaderas "
"relaciones causales."

#: ../source/notebooks/mmm/mmm_causal_identification.ipynb:10006
#: f1869d70c0e74885a15a32e3a9b13d90
msgid ""
"Note: Inspired by the notebook from [Bridging Causal Thinking and Media Mix "
"Models: Carlos Trujillo & Ben "
"Vincent](https://colab.research.google.com/drive/1r5pi9Lh_A6h_CKQFEjyn-7iykL8x-X_H#scrollTo=DRFEJyK1VCi3)."
msgstr ""
"Nota: Inspirado en el cuaderno de [Bridging Causal Thinking and Media Mix "
"Models: Carlos Trujillo & Ben "
"Vincent](https://colab.research.google.com/drive/1r5pi9Lh_A6h_CKQFEjyn-7iykL8x-X_H#scrollTo=DRFEJyK1VCi3)."

#: ../source/notebooks/mmm/mmm_causal_identification.ipynb:10008
#: 66bcf5f86db047308e27bd88b14d405e
msgid "Why Is Understanding Causal Relationships Important in Regressions?"
msgstr ""
"¿Por qué es importante entender las relaciones causales en las regresiones?"

#: ../source/notebooks/mmm/mmm_causal_identification.ipynb:10010
#: 3cd70c372337466c939308b873a474a1
msgid ""
"In regression models, we often aim to estimate how one or more factors "
"affect an outcome. However, if we don't consider causality carefully, our "
"estimates can be biased due to:"
msgstr ""
"En los modelos de regresión, a menudo buscamos estimar cómo uno o más "
"factores afectan un resultado. Sin embargo, si no consideramos la causalidad"
" con cuidado, nuestras estimaciones pueden estar sesgadas debido a:"

#: ../source/notebooks/mmm/mmm_causal_identification.ipynb:10012
#: 34fd666c74fe48aca7a3164d12a1c627
msgid ""
"**Confounding Bias**: This happens when a hidden factor influences both the "
"predictor and the outcome, leading to misleading connections."
msgstr ""
"**Sesgo confuso**: Esto ocurre cuando un factor oculto influye tanto en el "
"predictor como en el resultado, lo que lleva a conexiones engañosas."

#: ../source/notebooks/mmm/mmm_causal_identification.ipynb:10013
#: 6b26b1d464f84ecf938c3890b5de3b96
msgid ""
"**Selection Bias**: When we use non-random samples, this can distort the "
"estimated relationships."
msgstr ""
"**Sesgo de Selección**: Cuando utilizamos muestras no aleatorias, esto puede"
" distorsionar las relaciones estimadas."

#: ../source/notebooks/mmm/mmm_causal_identification.ipynb:10014
#: f2ff313038834bc387b288272c301686
msgid ""
"**Overcontrol**: Adjusting for variables that are influenced by the "
"treatment can lead to incorrect estimates of causal effects."
msgstr ""
"**Sobrecontrol**: Ajustar las variables que son influenciadas por el "
"tratamiento puede llevar a estimaciones incorrectas de los efectos causales."

#: ../source/notebooks/mmm/mmm_causal_identification.ipynb:10016
#: 0405e9bda63d42b686ce2a76d89fc4b4
msgid ""
"Causal identification helps us adjust the right variables in the regression "
"to isolate the true effect by addressing confounders and avoiding "
"unnecessary adjustments. Without it, we can run into several problems:"
msgstr ""
"La identificación causal nos ayuda a ajustar las variables adecuadas en la "
"regresión para aislar el verdadero efecto al abordar los factores de "
"confusión y evitar ajustes innecesarios. Sin ella, podemos enfrentar varios "
"problemas:"

#: ../source/notebooks/mmm/mmm_causal_identification.ipynb:10018
#: 29e335a6116d402fa4caa9a52f990173
msgid ""
"**Bias in Estimates**: Our understanding of effect size and direction might "
"be wrong, which can lead to poor decisions."
msgstr ""
"**Sesgo en las estimaciones**: Nuestra comprensión del tamaño y la dirección"
" del efecto puede ser incorrecta, lo que puede llevar a decisiones "
"equivocadas."

#: ../source/notebooks/mmm/mmm_causal_identification.ipynb:10019
#: 00dfab1667d0471ba8881e21de35a6ed
msgid ""
"**Spurious Correlations**: We might misinterpret coincidental relationships "
"as causal."
msgstr ""
"**Correlaciones Espurias**: Podríamos malinterpretar relaciones coincidentes"
" como causales."

#: ../source/notebooks/mmm/mmm_causal_identification.ipynb:10020
#: 7fde755a2a754eca81f6924234d7158b
msgid ""
"**Inefficient Models**: Including irrelevant variables or missing important "
"confounders can weaken the model’s accuracy and clarity."
msgstr ""
"**Modelos Ineficientes**: Incluir variables irrelevantes o faltar variables "
"de confusión importantes puede debilitar la precisión y claridad del modelo."

#: ../source/notebooks/mmm/mmm_causal_identification.ipynb:10022
#: 238a5ae818bc44f982b8b839451f646c
msgid ""
"In media mix modeling (MMM), where businesses allocate budgets across "
"different channels to maximize returns, these issues can lead to poor "
"resource allocation, wasted money, or misattributing success to ineffective "
"strategies."
msgstr ""
"En la modelización de mezcla de medios (MMM), donde las empresas asignan "
"presupuestos a diferentes canales para maximizar los retornos, estos "
"problemas pueden llevar a una mala asignación de recursos, dinero "
"desperdiciado o a atribuir erróneamente el éxito a estrategias ineficaces."

#: ../source/notebooks/mmm/mmm_causal_identification.ipynb:10024
#: 0b4425fc18544d96a05673a2585066f8
msgid "Key Concepts in This Notebook"
msgstr "Conceptos clave en este cuaderno"

#: ../source/notebooks/mmm/mmm_causal_identification.ipynb:10026
#: 23172bae6dea45b1a00deaaf44a1bfcc
msgid "This notebook covers key ideas in causal inference, including:"
msgstr "Este cuaderno abarca ideas clave en la inferencia causal, incluyendo:"

#: ../source/notebooks/mmm/mmm_causal_identification.ipynb:10028
#: 1af82860a5424f0aa21bd625818ba51e
msgid ""
"**Causal Directed Acyclic Graphs (DAGs)**: These are visual tools that show "
"the assumed causal relationships in the data."
msgstr ""
"**Grafos Acíclicos Dirigidos Causales (DAGs)**: Estas son herramientas "
"visuales que muestran las relaciones causales asumidas en los datos."

#: ../source/notebooks/mmm/mmm_causal_identification.ipynb:10029
#: fc3323e665cc4822939556aa17557eb4
msgid ""
"**Backdoor Criterion**: This rule helps identify which variables block paths"
" that create misleading connections between the treatment and outcome."
msgstr ""
"**Criterio de Puerta Trasera**: Esta regla ayuda a identificar qué variables"
" bloquean los caminos que crean conexiones engañosas entre el tratamiento y "
"el resultado."

#: ../source/notebooks/mmm/mmm_causal_identification.ipynb:10030
#: 5fc2ddc702434c7cbdd35a633c71ead9
msgid ""
"**Minimal Adjustment Set**: This is the smallest group of factors needed to "
"meet the backdoor criterion, ensuring accurate causal estimates."
msgstr ""
"**Conjunto de Ajuste Mínimo**: Este es el grupo más pequeño de factores "
"necesarios para cumplir con el criterio de puerta trasera, asegurando "
"estimaciones causales precisas."

#: ../source/notebooks/mmm/mmm_causal_identification.ipynb:10032
#: acb8e28f92e14945a2a3d954aa46c318
msgid ""
"These tools help us understand causal inference more clearly and give us "
"solid guidelines for choosing variables in media mix models."
msgstr ""
"Estas herramientas nos ayudan a comprender la inferencia causal de manera "
"más clara y nos brindan pautas sólidas para elegir variables en modelos de "
"mezcla de medios."

#: ../source/notebooks/mmm/mmm_causal_identification.ipynb:10034
#: f16bd037ee284792b3089cf8ef00ed54
msgid ""
"By the end of this notebook, you will learn how to use `pymc-marketing` "
"alongside causal thinking principles for effective media mix modeling."
msgstr ""
"Al final de este cuaderno, aprenderá a utilizar `pymc-marketing` junto con "
"los principios del pensamiento causal para un modelado efectivo de la mezcla"
" de medios."

#: ../source/notebooks/mmm/mmm_causal_identification.ipynb:10036
#: 9debd282a43c47298bc43d6fdde4494a
msgid "Let’s start by importing the necessary libraries!"
msgstr "¡Comencemos importando las bibliotecas necesarias!"

#: ../source/notebooks/mmm/mmm_causal_identification.ipynb:60002
#: 3a779c8e654240a5be5cbf67cb3fa359
msgid "Business problem"
msgstr "Problema empresarial"

#: ../source/notebooks/mmm/mmm_causal_identification.ipynb:60004
#: 705c55e16cb84980bf55e3e012186073
msgid ""
"Imagine you run a retail company that advertises its products. You've been "
"in business for a while and have noticed steady sales growth. During "
"holidays, sales increase even more. However, you're not the only one "
"advertising; a competitor is also promoting their products, likely with "
"discounts or special offers."
msgstr ""
"Imagina que diriges una empresa minorista que publicita sus productos. Has "
"estado en el negocio durante un tiempo y has notado un crecimiento constante"
" en las ventas. Durante las festividades, las ventas aumentan aún más. Sin "
"embargo, no eres el único que publicita; un competidor también está "
"promoviendo sus productos, probablemente con descuentos u ofertas "
"especiales."

#: ../source/notebooks/mmm/mmm_causal_identification.ipynb:60006
#: 35cab566c71c409d9466255ddd7a50a1
msgid "Let's explore how different factors relate to each other:"
msgstr "Exploremos cómo se relacionan entre sí diferentes factores:"

#: ../source/notebooks/mmm/mmm_causal_identification.ipynb:60008
#: a1daa6cd5bf64df58db8fbbe361ac2ee
msgid ""
"**Christmas (C)**: The holiday season boosts consumer interest, leading to "
"more ad views (X1 and X2) and directly increasing your sales (T)."
msgstr ""
"**Navidad (C)**: La temporada navideña incrementa el interés del consumidor,"
" lo que lleva a más visualizaciones de anuncios (X1 y X2) y aumenta "
"directamente sus ventas (T)."

#: ../source/notebooks/mmm/mmm_causal_identification.ipynb:60009
#: 3ccec839603a4d07842b3d6f8fa00fcb
msgid "**Marketing Channels (X1, X2)**:"
msgstr "**Canales de Marketing (X1, X2)**:"

#: ../source/notebooks/mmm/mmm_causal_identification.ipynb:60010
#: ae1d778ac43f4506a2a96d9d771737b6
msgid "**X1**: Social media ads, like those on Facebook or TikTok."
msgstr "**X1**: Anuncios en redes sociales, como los de Facebook o TikTok."

#: ../source/notebooks/mmm/mmm_causal_identification.ipynb:60011
#: 41b12b18ab61497dba817077794372a4
msgid ""
"**X2**: Search engine ads, which can enhance the impact of social media ads "
"(these channels work well together)."
msgstr ""
"**X2**: Anuncios en motores de búsqueda, que pueden aumentar el impacto de "
"los anuncios en redes sociales (estos canales funcionan bien juntos)."

#: ../source/notebooks/mmm/mmm_causal_identification.ipynb:60012
#: 2b611cccf17648d5b4cefe16c03b0ac7
msgid "**Target (T)**: Your goal is to maximize sales revenue."
msgstr "**Objetivo (T)**: Su meta es maximizar los ingresos por ventas."

#: ../source/notebooks/mmm/mmm_causal_identification.ipynb:60013
#: 11f5cafc78dd4d1b9bfed977cc284c04
msgid "**Unseen Factors**:"
msgstr "**Factores no visibles**:"

#: ../source/notebooks/mmm/mmm_causal_identification.ipynb:60014
#: 5b991ab60eff4940ab7c2645bb2db3f6
msgid ""
"**Competitor Offers (I)**: Your competitor may run aggressive holiday "
"discounts, which could lessen the impact of your search ads (X2) and reduce "
"your sales (T)."
msgstr ""
"**Ofertas de Competidores (I)**: Su competidor puede ofrecer descuentos "
"agresivos durante las festividades, lo que podría disminuir el impacto de "
"sus anuncios de búsqueda (X2) y reducir sus ventas (T)."

#: ../source/notebooks/mmm/mmm_causal_identification.ipynb:60015
#: 41ac17a5ea2244ec908a163b367c292d
msgid ""
"**Market Growth (G)**: Economic growth during the holiday season might boost"
" sales (T) regardless of your advertising efforts."
msgstr ""
"**Crecimiento del Mercado (G)**: El crecimiento económico durante la "
"temporada navideña podría impulsar las ventas (T) independientemente de sus "
"esfuerzos publicitarios."

#: ../source/notebooks/mmm/mmm_causal_identification.ipynb:60017
#: 3f05387c7b384b9a90cb5ea89f8aa65c
msgid "Visualizing Relationships with a DAG"
msgstr "Visualizando relaciones con un DAG"

#: ../source/notebooks/mmm/mmm_causal_identification.ipynb:60019
#: c6628f64230d486d85011484bcb36177
msgid "We can illustrate these ideas using a Directed Acyclic Graph (DAG)."
msgstr ""
"Podemos ilustrar estas ideas utilizando un Grafo Acíclico Dirigido (DAG)."

#: ../source/notebooks/mmm/mmm_causal_identification.ipynb:80002
#: 62593bfe4ac04c22b21a47b0ac416e15
msgid "Observed Factors:"
msgstr "Factores observados:"

#: ../source/notebooks/mmm/mmm_causal_identification.ipynb:80003
#: 59c13f931866462c8a5ad4b398895415
msgid ""
"**Marketing Impressions X1 and X2**: Two channels (search ads and social "
"ads) that can affect sales (T). They can also impact each other."
msgstr ""
"**Impresiones de Marketing X1 y X2**: Dos canales (anuncios de búsqueda y "
"anuncios en redes sociales) que pueden afectar las ventas (T). También "
"pueden influirse mutuamente."

#: ../source/notebooks/mmm/mmm_causal_identification.ipynb:80004
#: 55a9dc50e024436a905c42099282a053
msgid ""
"**Target (T)**: The key metric you want to improve, like sales revenue."
msgstr ""
"**Objetivo (T)**: La métrica clave que desea mejorar, como los ingresos por "
"ventas."

#: ../source/notebooks/mmm/mmm_causal_identification.ipynb:80006
#: 4bf6284e1ab3443391e26949b6d79461
msgid "Unseen Factors (Dashed Elements):"
msgstr "Factores no visibles (Elementos discontinuos):"

#: ../source/notebooks/mmm/mmm_causal_identification.ipynb:80007
#: cbedd673b2874e889190562e0bdb5a89
msgid ""
"**Christmas (C)**: A seasonal event that influences both marketing "
"impressions (X1, X2) and sales (T)."
msgstr ""
"**Navidad (C)**: Un evento estacional que influye tanto en las impresiones "
"de marketing (X1, X2) como en las ventas (T)."

#: ../source/notebooks/mmm/mmm_causal_identification.ipynb:80008
#: db1e1855f8b349f492be1b576c199ff6
msgid ""
"**Competitor Offers (I)**: Actions by competitors, such as discounts, which "
"can influence marketing channels and sales."
msgstr ""
"**Ofertas de Competidores (I)**: Acciones de los competidores, como "
"descuentos, que pueden influir en los canales de marketing y en las ventas."

#: ../source/notebooks/mmm/mmm_causal_identification.ipynb:80009
#: 0f391c01f13749f4ad2967d9a2d2c12c
msgid "**Market Growth (G)**: Broader economic trends that affect sales."
msgstr ""
"**Crecimiento del Mercado (G)**: Tendencias económicas más amplias que "
"afectan las ventas."

#: ../source/notebooks/mmm/mmm_causal_identification.ipynb:80011
#: 08d57e2b3510458297d6ace79d21c163
msgid ""
"Note: Dashed elements are not possible to intervene, on the other hand, "
"solid elements are possible to intervene."
msgstr ""
"Nota: Los elementos en línea discontinua no se pueden intervenir, mientras "
"que los elementos en línea continua sí se pueden intervenir."

#: ../source/notebooks/mmm/mmm_causal_identification.ipynb:80013
#: 75b7250f0e1944e59455b205c96e1b46
msgid "Key Relationships:"
msgstr "Relaciones Clave:"

#: ../source/notebooks/mmm/mmm_causal_identification.ipynb:80014
#: 2e9f7f2443e4451c89d050436688e1b6
msgid ""
"Christmas (C) boosts both marketing impressions (X1, X2) and directly "
"increases sales (T) during the holiday season."
msgstr ""
"La Navidad (C) impulsa tanto las impresiones de marketing (X1, X2) como "
"aumenta directamente las ventas (T) durante la temporada navideña."

#: ../source/notebooks/mmm/mmm_causal_identification.ipynb:80015
#: 8d59f862440647208487e8e408861379
msgid ""
"Marketing impressions (X1, X2) affect sales (T) through your advertising "
"efforts. X1 can help X2 (e.g., social ads support search ads)."
msgstr ""
"Las impresiones de marketing (X1, X2) afectan las ventas (T) a través de sus"
" esfuerzos publicitarios. X1 puede ayudar a X2 (por ejemplo, los anuncios en"
" redes sociales apoyan a los anuncios de búsqueda)."

#: ../source/notebooks/mmm/mmm_causal_identification.ipynb:80016
#: 4d899886a90940b48a4d92490a4ab341
msgid ""
"Competitor Offers (I) and Market Growth (G) impact the marketing channels "
"and sales, which can confuse the understanding of cause and effect."
msgstr ""
"Las Ofertas de Competidores (I) y el Crecimiento del Mercado (G) impactan "
"los canales de marketing y las ventas, lo que puede confundir la comprensión"
" de causa y efecto."

#: ../source/notebooks/mmm/mmm_causal_identification.ipynb:80018
#: ed9a3f6a586a4f3288938cd3bc3720c1
msgid ""
"We now need to define how these relationships work and create a model to "
"generate data that reflects these assumptions. This way, we can see how well"
" we can identify causal relationships using the data we gather."
msgstr ""
"Ahora necesitamos definir cómo funcionan estas relaciones y crear un modelo "
"para generar datos que reflejen estas suposiciones. De esta manera, podemos "
"ver qué tan bien podemos identificar relaciones causales utilizando los "
"datos que recopilamos."

#: ../source/notebooks/mmm/mmm_causal_identification.ipynb:100002
#: a780e7724eb94dd7b7f928546902b1ff
msgid ""
"We set a date range between January 2022 and November 2024, at a daily "
"frequency."
msgstr ""
"Establecimos un rango de fechas entre enero de 2022 y noviembre de 2024, con"
" una frecuencia diaria."

#: ../source/notebooks/mmm/mmm_causal_identification.ipynb:100004
#: 9cd354c6944a48b4b6e13ce572c7ad74
msgid "Generating the Market Growth (Trend)"
msgstr "Generando el Crecimiento del Mercado (Tendencia)"

#: ../source/notebooks/mmm/mmm_causal_identification.ipynb:100005
#: f33730cc48e04de2afc2fe4e20f71734
msgid ""
"Next, we generate the data for **market growth**. We assume the market "
"growth follows a power-law trend, meaning that growth accelerates over time "
"rather than remaining constant. This can be mathematically defined as:"
msgstr ""
"A continuación, generamos los datos para **el crecimiento del mercado**. "
"Asumimos que el crecimiento del mercado sigue una tendencia de ley de "
"potencias, lo que significa que el crecimiento se acelera con el tiempo en "
"lugar de permanecer constante. Esto se puede definir matemáticamente como:"

#: ../source/notebooks/mmm/mmm_causal_identification.ipynb:100007
#: 6d27103eadc746abb37636ffc280ce97
msgid ""
"\n"
"MG_{t} = (t + \\text{baseline})^{\\text{exponent}} - 1\n"
msgstr "MG_{t} = (t + \\text{baseline})^{\\text{exponent}} - 1"

#: ../source/notebooks/mmm/mmm_causal_identification.ipynb:100011
#: ../source/notebooks/mmm/mmm_causal_identification.ipynb:120012
#: ../source/notebooks/mmm/mmm_causal_identification.ipynb:140010
#: ../source/notebooks/mmm/mmm_causal_identification.ipynb:220012
#: ../source/notebooks/mmm/mmm_causal_identification.ipynb:580030
#: 45d4071522444991a9cb2b0dfb4fa6cd 6ffb769ea6ef4c94ba9b665caf1cc229
#: 96d5cc31ca1f404e9e32b63dc6d253da b7321374e23541ca8f72dbbac09bd421
#: f71d139db9b64ac1a5dd7ee29290f321
msgid "Where:"
msgstr "Dónde:"

#: ../source/notebooks/mmm/mmm_causal_identification.ipynb:100012
#: dcb3aea42ccf4ba09ed95775e42746ae
msgid ""
"$t$: The time index, representing days since the start of the date range."
msgstr ""
"$t$: El índice de tiempo, que representa los días desde el inicio del rango "
"de fechas."

#: ../source/notebooks/mmm/mmm_causal_identification.ipynb:100013
#: 6bac8e5fa91e4db2b2a31ba01af8c93f
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"$baseline$: A constant added to $t$ to shift the starting point of the "
"trend. This value affects the initial level of market growth. The starting "
"value of the function will be $(baseline)^{exponent} - 1$, not 0."
msgstr ""
"$baseline$: Una constante añadida a $t$ para desplazar el punto de inicio de"
" la tendencia. Este valor afecta el nivel inicial del crecimiento del "
"mercado. El valor inicial de la función será $(baseline)^{exponent} - 1$, no"
" 0."

#: ../source/notebooks/mmm/mmm_causal_identification.ipynb:100014
#: 5d93302b241448ecb27f2e42f8d5ede1
msgid ""
"$exponent$: The power to which the time index is raised, determining the "
"rate at which the trend accelerates over time."
msgstr ""
"$exponent$: La potencia a la que se eleva el índice de tiempo, determinando "
"la tasa a la que la tendencia se acelera con el tiempo."

#: ../source/notebooks/mmm/mmm_causal_identification.ipynb:120002
#: c7bbfb71b59f4ca88a7120d84ff10dce
msgid "Generating the Holiday Effect"
msgstr "Generando el Efecto Vacacional"

#: ../source/notebooks/mmm/mmm_causal_identification.ipynb:120004
#: 624b411341444e64bc85010a333e2bb2
msgid ""
"In this section, we simulate the effect of holidays on the market growth "
"trend. Certain holidays, like Christmas, can have a significant impact on "
"consumer behavior, leading to seasonal spikes in sales. To capture these "
"effects, we introduce a holiday signal based on Gaussian (normal) "
"distributions centered around specific holiday dates."
msgstr ""
"En esta sección, simulamos el efecto de las festividades en la tendencia de "
"crecimiento del mercado. Ciertas festividades, como la Navidad, pueden tener"
" un impacto significativo en el comportamiento del consumidor, lo que lleva "
"a picos estacionales en las ventas. Para capturar estos efectos, "
"introducimos una señal de festividad basada en distribuciones gaussianas "
"(normales) centradas en fechas específicas de festividades."

#: ../source/notebooks/mmm/mmm_causal_identification.ipynb:120006
#: 88d11c86dff44efbb4be49eb5935dab9
msgid "The function used to model the holiday effect is defined as follows:"
msgstr ""
"La función utilizada para modelar el efecto de las vacaciones se define de "
"la siguiente manera:"

#: ../source/notebooks/mmm/mmm_causal_identification.ipynb:120008
#: 25e4ec16b3b54d15b2c6210f02e2781e
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"\n"
"H_{t} = \\exp\\left(-0.5 \\left(\\frac{\\Delta t}{\\sigma}\\right)^2\\right)\n"
msgstr "H_{t} = \\exp\\left(-0.5 \\left(\\frac{\\Delta t}{\\sigma}\\right)^2\\right)"

#: ../source/notebooks/mmm/mmm_causal_identification.ipynb:120013
#: f16e1976c06f47d095f2d53c5e909e78
msgid ""
"$\\Delta t$ is the time difference (in days) between the current date and "
"the holiday date."
msgstr ""
"$\\Delta t$ es la diferencia de tiempo (en días) entre la fecha actual y la "
"fecha de la festividad."

#: ../source/notebooks/mmm/mmm_causal_identification.ipynb:120014
#: 7043e36050354a2cb27e5438a6952166
msgid ""
"$\\sigma$ is the standard deviation that controls the spread of the effect "
"around the holiday date."
msgstr ""
"$\\sigma$ es la desviación estándar que controla la dispersión del efecto "
"alrededor de la fecha de la festividad."

#: ../source/notebooks/mmm/mmm_causal_identification.ipynb:120016
#: 9b840fa54c914dd688d6d1f682b19e45
msgid ""
"For each holiday, we calculate the holiday signal across the date range and "
"add a **holiday contribution** by scaling the signal with a holiday-specific"
" coefficient. This approach models seasonal holiday spikes using Gaussian "
"functions, which capture the transient increase in market activity around "
"holidays, and their respective decay over time."
msgstr ""
"Para cada festividad, calculamos la señal de la festividad a lo largo del "
"rango de fechas y añadimos una **contribución de festividad** escalando la "
"señal con un coeficiente específico de la festividad. Este enfoque modela "
"los picos estacionales de las festividades utilizando funciones gaussianas, "
"que capturan el aumento transitorio en la actividad del mercado alrededor de"
" las festividades y su respectivo decaimiento a lo largo del tiempo."

#: ../source/notebooks/mmm/mmm_causal_identification.ipynb:140002
#: d222602cbcb543dc8d7a04abe402eef5
msgid "Modeling Competitor Offers"
msgstr "Modelando Ofertas de Competidores"

#: ../source/notebooks/mmm/mmm_causal_identification.ipynb:140004
#: 25f05d706d0348b8a52d1e80e7022498
msgid "To simulate the impact of competitor offers on market growth."
msgstr ""
"Para simular el impacto de las ofertas de los competidores en el crecimiento"
" del mercado."

#: ../source/notebooks/mmm/mmm_causal_identification.ipynb:140006
#: 27333fc87221449e84e82a2efa448060
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"\n"
"C_{t} = -A \\cdot \\cos(\\omega \\cdot t) + C\n"
msgstr "C_{t} = -A \\cdot \\cos(\\omega \\cdot t) + C"

#: ../source/notebooks/mmm/mmm_causal_identification.ipynb:140011
#: 07d0b3624e0a48908dabf4166cda84c4
msgid ""
"$A$: The **amplitude** of the oscillation, representing the maximum "
"deviation from the center. In this context, it controls the intensity of the"
" competitor offers."
msgstr ""
"$A$: La **amplitud** de la oscilación, que representa la desviación máxima "
"del centro. En este contexto, controla la intensidad de las ofertas de los "
"competidores."

#: ../source/notebooks/mmm/mmm_causal_identification.ipynb:140012
#: 5b7fffd4b1a34bc28dc9ab0a0ffe8d10
msgid ""
"$C$: The **center of oscillation**, setting the average level around which "
"competitor offers fluctuate."
msgstr ""
"$C$: El **centro de oscilación**, que establece el nivel promedio alrededor "
"del cual fluctúan las ofertas de los competidores."

#: ../source/notebooks/mmm/mmm_causal_identification.ipynb:140013
#: c403c2efdc5c411db2dd54e2babfdcb5
msgid ""
"$\\omega$: The **angular frequency**, which determines the frequency of the "
"oscillations. It’s calculated as: $\\omega = \\frac{\\pi}{\\frac{n}{2}}$ "
"where $n$ is the total number of data points. This ensures a complete cycle "
"within the specified range."
msgstr ""
"$\\omega$: La **frecuencia angular**, que determina la frecuencia de las "
"oscilaciones. Se calcula como: $\\omega = \\frac{\\pi}{\\frac{n}{2}}$ donde "
"$n$ es el número total de puntos de datos. Esto asegura un ciclo completo "
"dentro del rango especificado."

#: ../source/notebooks/mmm/mmm_causal_identification.ipynb:160002
#: 70e3d1c8d273472d8413cd5374204dc7
msgid ""
"With this form, we simulate a world where competitors offers increase during"
" the initial days of the year, and then decrease towards the end of the "
"year."
msgstr ""
"Con este formulario, simulamos un mundo donde las ofertas de los "
"competidores aumentan durante los primeros días del año y luego disminuyen "
"hacia el final del año."

#: ../source/notebooks/mmm/mmm_causal_identification.ipynb:160004
#: 4219f4e7e0814486983064f1573fa925
msgid "Modeling Marketing Channels"
msgstr "Modelando Canales de Marketing"

#: ../source/notebooks/mmm/mmm_causal_identification.ipynb:160006
#: 56d194f3aea041fca23ccbe81ef23084
msgid ""
"In this section, we simulate two marketing channels, $x1$ and $x2$, which "
"represent different advertising channels (e.g., Search ads and Social media "
"campaigns). Each channel's behavior is influenced by random variability and "
"confounding effects from seasonal holidays and competitor actions. Here’s "
"how we model each channel mathematically:"
msgstr ""
"En esta sección, simulamos dos canales de marketing, $x1$ y $x2$, que "
"representan diferentes canales publicitarios (por ejemplo, anuncios de "
"búsqueda y campañas en redes sociales). El comportamiento de cada canal está"
" influenciado por la variabilidad aleatoria y los efectos confusos de las "
"festividades estacionales y las acciones de los competidores. Así es como "
"modelamos cada canal matemáticamente:"

#: ../source/notebooks/mmm/mmm_causal_identification.ipynb:160008
#: 758f32029a704b72b5ce3881d6ac9223
msgid ""
"**Channel $x1$**: As mentioned before, we generate $x1$ which is affected by"
" the holiday signal, we could define it as:"
msgstr ""
"**Canal $x1$**: Como se mencionó anteriormente, generamos $x1$ que se ve "
"afectado por la señal de vacaciones, podríamos definirlo como:"

#: ../source/notebooks/mmm/mmm_causal_identification.ipynb:160011
#: fa1cc7da514a48f598bd00382be800b6
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"\n"
"I_{x1_t} = S_{x1_t} + H_{t} \\times \\alpha_{x1}\n"
msgstr "I_{x1_t} = S_{x1_t} + H_{t} \\times \\alpha_{x1}"

#: ../source/notebooks/mmm/mmm_causal_identification.ipynb:160015
#: 7ff75f20b66a430abc982eb29a8b4387
msgid ""
"**Channel $x2$**: On the other hand, we generate $x2$ which is affected by "
"the holiday signal, the influence of $x1$ and the competitor offers. We "
"could define it as:"
msgstr ""
"**Canal $x2$**: Por otro lado, generamos $x2$ que se ve afectado por la "
"señal de vacaciones, la influencia de $x1$ y las ofertas de los "
"competidores. Podríamos definirlo como:"

#: ../source/notebooks/mmm/mmm_causal_identification.ipynb:160018
#: 3cbedfc36be345ff9c66daef47d24ed8
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"\n"
"I_{x2_t} = S_{x2_t} + H_{t} \\times \\alpha_{x2} + (I_{x1_t} \\times \\alpha_{x1_x2}) + (C_{t} \\times \\alpha_{x2})\n"
msgstr ""
"I_{x2_t} = S_{x2_t} + H_{t} \\times \\alpha_{x2} + (I_{x1_t} \\times "
"\\alpha_{x1_x2}) + (C_{t} \\times \\alpha_{x2})"

#: ../source/notebooks/mmm/mmm_causal_identification.ipynb:160022
#: c8abd2a052384fff9b2d0cde2f9624e2
msgid "Interpretation"
msgstr "Interpretación"

#: ../source/notebooks/mmm/mmm_causal_identification.ipynb:160024
#: f26400d09a1d48ef9a425f1806e60d75
msgid ""
"These equations allow us to capture the complex dynamics influencing each "
"marketing channel:"
msgstr ""
"Estas ecuaciones nos permiten capturar la dinámica compleja que influye en "
"cada canal de marketing:"

#: ../source/notebooks/mmm/mmm_causal_identification.ipynb:160025
#: 422b0365fd27440eb211a3e4e99a3a5e
msgid ""
"**Holiday Effects** increase channel activity around specific dates, "
"simulating seasonal spikes."
msgstr ""
"**Efectos de Vacaciones** aumentan la actividad del canal alrededor de "
"fechas específicas, simulando picos estacionales."

#: ../source/notebooks/mmm/mmm_causal_identification.ipynb:160026
#: a458ffd133cb4970a30b6a9151b847ac
msgid ""
"**Cross-channel Influences** introduce interdependencies, modeling how one "
"channel's success can amplify another’s."
msgstr ""
"**Influencias entre canales** introducen interdependencias, modelando cómo "
"el éxito de un canal puede amplificar el de otro."

#: ../source/notebooks/mmm/mmm_causal_identification.ipynb:160027
#: 88aabd0530ae4901bd00544c37237a34
msgid ""
"**Competitor Effects** introduce fluctuations due to external factors, "
"showing how competitive pressure can decrease engagement or effectiveness."
msgstr ""
"**Efectos de la competencia** introducen fluctuaciones debido a factores "
"externos, mostrando cómo la presión competitiva puede disminuir el "
"compromiso o la efectividad."

#: ../source/notebooks/mmm/mmm_causal_identification.ipynb:160029
#: 57ea2abbea1a44a6a7e881900599567b
msgid ""
"This approach reflects real-world conditions, where marketing channels are "
"not isolated but affected by seasonal trends, competitor actions, and "
"synergies across different channels."
msgstr ""
"Este enfoque refleja las condiciones del mundo real, donde los canales de "
"marketing no están aislados, sino que se ven afectados por tendencias "
"estacionales, acciones de los competidores y sinergias entre diferentes "
"canales."

#: ../source/notebooks/mmm/mmm_causal_identification.ipynb:190002
#: c721c58759ca417f9385f446f5964c0d
msgid ""
"The two generated signals wil represent the \"impressions\" of the two "
"marketing channels. Basically, we are simulating the exposure that we would "
"observe from a media platform, reported after we run a campaign."
msgstr ""
"Las dos señales generadas representarán las \"impresiones\" de los dos "
"canales de marketing. Básicamente, estamos simulando la exposición que "
"observaríamos de una plataforma de medios, reportada después de ejecutar una"
" campaña."

#: ../source/notebooks/mmm/mmm_causal_identification.ipynb:190004
#: 19b309d70dbc4a4ab7991febffa87d26
msgid ""
"The level of exposure doesn't impact our sales in a linear way, so we need "
"to apply a transformation to account for that. We'll use a geometric adstock"
" transformation, which is a common technique in marketing mix modeling to "
"account for the adstock/lagging effect, and a michaelis-menten saturation to"
" account for the diminishing returns effect."
msgstr ""
"El nivel de exposición no impacta nuestras ventas de manera lineal, por lo "
"que necesitamos aplicar una transformación para tenerlo en cuenta. "
"Utilizaremos una transformación de adstock geométrico, que es una técnica "
"común en la modelización de mezcla de marketing para considerar el efecto de"
" adstock/retraso, y una saturación de michaelis-menten para tener en cuenta "
"el efecto de rendimientos decrecientes."

#: ../source/notebooks/mmm/mmm_causal_identification.ipynb:190006
#: e2e4a9924d4d4015972ad66881665863
msgid ""
"Similar as the [initial example in pymc-"
"marketing](https://docs.pymc.io/notebooks/mmm/mmm_initial_example.html)."
msgstr ""
"Similar al [ejemplo inicial en pymc-"
"marketing](https://docs.pymc.io/notebooks/mmm/mmm_initial_example.html)."

#: ../source/notebooks/mmm/mmm_causal_identification.ipynb:220002
#: bef5a7eec8774391a7a38d2879edff28
msgid "Defining the Sales (Target)"
msgstr "Definiendo las Ventas (Objetivo)"

#: ../source/notebooks/mmm/mmm_causal_identification.ipynb:220004
#: 3168c469f8f3459fb1c881f1d8e78bc1
msgid ""
"Finally, we define the sales or revenue (target) variable, which is affected"
" by the market growth, the competitor offers, the holiday contributions, the"
" saturated media costs and a noise term."
msgstr ""
"Finalmente, definimos la variable de ventas o ingresos (objetivo), que se ve"
" afectada por el crecimiento del mercado, las ofertas de los competidores, "
"las contribuciones de las festividades, los costos de medios saturados y un "
"término de ruido."

#: ../source/notebooks/mmm/mmm_causal_identification.ipynb:220006
#: de15ad9e745e4412b7aaed2246b31618
msgid "The variable, $y$, is defined as follows:"
msgstr "La variable, $y$, se define de la siguiente manera:"

#: ../source/notebooks/mmm/mmm_causal_identification.ipynb:220008
#: f3191a3d25f34c2693706185ffd55235
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"\n"
"y_{t} = Intercept + f(MG_{t}) - f(C_{t}) + f(H_{t}) + m(I_{x1_t}) + m(I_{x2_t}) + \\epsilon\n"
msgstr ""
"y_{t} = Intercepto + f(MG_{t}) - f(C_{t}) + f(H_{t}) + m(I_{x1_t}) + "
"m(I_{x2_t}) + \\epsilon"

#: ../source/notebooks/mmm/mmm_causal_identification.ipynb:220013
#: d1e8bd52491c4531ad7f7510cfe993b6
msgid ""
"**Intercept**: A baseline level of sales, set to 1.5, representing the base "
"sales level in the absence of other effects."
msgstr ""
"**Intercepto**: Un nivel base de ventas, establecido en 1.5, que representa "
"el nivel base de ventas en ausencia de otros efectos."

#: ../source/notebooks/mmm/mmm_causal_identification.ipynb:220014
#: 05e558f7d48e417aa8aae983c5d4a2af
msgid ""
"**Market Growth**: Represents the underlying trend in sales due to long-term"
" growth, with an implicit coefficient of 1, adding a steady upward "
"influence."
msgstr ""
"**Crecimiento del Mercado**: Representa la tendencia subyacente en las "
"ventas debido al crecimiento a largo plazo, con un coeficiente implícito de "
"1, añadiendo una influencia ascendente constante."

#: ../source/notebooks/mmm/mmm_causal_identification.ipynb:220015
#: 2dedf059af034eb58d802cc50b16c05a
msgid ""
"**Competitor Offers**: Directly reduces sales, with an implicit coefficient "
"of -1, simulating the negative impact of competitor actions on the target "
"variable."
msgstr ""
"**Ofertas de Competidores**: Reduce directamente las ventas, con un "
"coeficiente implícito de -1, simulando el impacto negativo de las acciones "
"de los competidores en la variable objetivo."

#: ../source/notebooks/mmm/mmm_causal_identification.ipynb:220016
#: 44300c63186149e8992d8592b090e624
msgid ""
"**Holiday Contributions**: Adds sales spikes around holiday periods, "
"capturing the seasonal increase in consumer demand."
msgstr ""
"**Contribuciones Festivas**: Añade picos de ventas durante los períodos "
"festivos, capturando el aumento estacional en la demanda del consumidor."

#: ../source/notebooks/mmm/mmm_causal_identification.ipynb:220017
#: 52a4ff19ca2d490bb348cc0dea41ec18
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"**$m(Impressions_{x1_t})$ and $m(Impressions_{x2_t})$**: Represent the "
"**saturated adstock** values for the marketing channels $x1$ and $x2$."
msgstr ""
"**$m(Impressions_{x1_t})$ y $m(Impressions_{x2_t})$**: Representan los "
"valores de **adstock saturado** para los canales de marketing $x1$ y $x2$."

#: ../source/notebooks/mmm/mmm_causal_identification.ipynb:220018
#: 377bc336ad5243d8a5da4daa4b5c8a42
msgid ""
"**Noise $\\epsilon$**: A small random error term, drawn from a normal "
"distribution with mean 0 and standard deviation 0.08, to account for "
"unexplained variability in sales."
msgstr ""
"**Ruido $\\epsilon$**: Un pequeño término de error aleatorio, extraído de "
"una distribución normal con media 0 y desviación estándar 0.08, para tener "
"en cuenta la variabilidad no explicada en las ventas."

#: ../source/notebooks/mmm/mmm_causal_identification.ipynb:250002
#: 05f7a94bd80845b8a64042bbc82a59ff
msgid "Let’s recap what we’ve done so far:"
msgstr "Hagamos un resumen de lo que hemos hecho hasta ahora:"

#: ../source/notebooks/mmm/mmm_causal_identification.ipynb:250004
