msgid ""
"At this point, we might feel like we have lost everything. It may seem that "
"some kind of bad luck is affecting our data. Or, we could have an unknown "
"factor that is influencing our marketing results without our notice."
msgstr ""
"En este punto, podríamos sentir que hemos perdido todo. Puede parecer que "
"algún tipo de mala suerte está afectando nuestros datos. O, podríamos tener "
"un factor desconocido que está influyendo en nuestros resultados de "
"marketing sin que nos demos cuenta."

#: ../source/notebooks/mmm/mmm_causal_identification.ipynb:580004
#: ab2fec1face448239dee758c4bdda715
msgid ""
"After some reflection, we can consider that our competitors’ actions, like "
"their offers and discounts, could be impacting our marketing results. In "
"other words, when our competitors spend more on marketing, they can take "
"away some of our potential incremental sales. Even if we spend the same "
"amount to get exposure, aggressive competitor offers can pull customers away"
" from us as they buy other products instead."
msgstr ""
"Después de una reflexión, podemos considerar que las acciones de nuestros "
"competidores, como sus ofertas y descuentos, podrían estar impactando "
"nuestros resultados de marketing. En otras palabras, cuando nuestros "
"competidores gastan más en marketing, pueden llevarse algunas de nuestras "
"posibles ventas incrementales. Incluso si gastamos la misma cantidad para "
"obtener exposición, las ofertas agresivas de los competidores pueden desviar"
" a los clientes de nosotros mientras compran otros productos en su lugar."

#: ../source/notebooks/mmm/mmm_causal_identification.ipynb:580006
#: 9cf0a694767d42aeb1842017fee7d983
msgid ""
"Will this affect all our channels the same way? Probably not. Our "
"competitors may not impact our brand awareness, but they likely influence "
"our customers’ consideration. We might think that $x2$ is more affected by "
"our competitors than $x1$. This is because $x2$ is closer to the purchase "
"decision, while $x1$ relates more to brand exposure."
msgstr ""
"¿Afectará esto a todos nuestros canales de la misma manera? Probablemente "
"no. Nuestros competidores pueden no impactar nuestra notoriedad de marca, "
"pero probablemente influyen en la consideración de nuestros clientes. "
"Podríamos pensar que $x2$ está más afectado por nuestros competidores que "
"$x1$. Esto se debe a que $x2$ está más cerca de la decisión de compra, "
"mientras que $x1$ se relaciona más con la exposición de la marca."

#: ../source/notebooks/mmm/mmm_causal_identification.ipynb:580008
#: 1b6a343dc34449ad853b428306e3a0d7
msgid ""
"This suggests that ‘competitor_offers’ might be an unseen factor affecting "
"$x2$ but not $x1$. Formally, this means we could express $x2$ as a function "
"of ‘competitor_offers’ while $x1$ would not include this factor."
msgstr ""
"Esto sugiere que ‘competitor_offers’ podría ser un factor no visible que "
"afecta a $x2$ pero no a $x1$. Formalmente, esto significa que podríamos "
"expresar $x2$ como una función de ‘competitor_offers’ mientras que $x1$ no "
"incluiría este factor."

#: ../source/notebooks/mmm/mmm_causal_identification.ipynb:580010
#: c64eb9381f5444d79ecc87baa39e0f70
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"\n"
"x2 = f(competitor\\_offers) + f(x1) + f(Spend_{x2}) + f(holiday\\_signal) + \\epsilon\n"
msgstr ""
"x2 = f(ofertas\\_competidor) + f(x1) + f(Gasto_{x2}) + f(señal\\_vacacional)"
" + \\epsilon"

#: ../source/notebooks/mmm/mmm_causal_identification.ipynb:580014
#: 64be01b3aae8440d990cf2b6503eeeba
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"\n"
"x1 = f(Spend_{x1}) + f(holiday\\_signal) + \\epsilon\n"
msgstr "x1 = f(Gastar_{x1}) + f(señal\\_vacacional) + \\epsilon"

#: ../source/notebooks/mmm/mmm_causal_identification.ipynb:580018
#: caf5c0b1d9864754bc00bf106701b361
msgid ""
"This is a good approach for building our model. However, we need to add "
"‘competitor_offers’ to our model, and we currently have no data on our "
"competitors, so we need to think creatively."
msgstr ""
"Este es un buen enfoque para construir nuestro modelo. Sin embargo, "
"necesitamos añadir ‘competitor_offers’ a nuestro modelo, y actualmente no "
"tenemos datos sobre nuestros competidores, por lo que necesitamos pensar de "
"manera creativa."

#: ../source/notebooks/mmm/mmm_causal_identification.ipynb:580020
#: 879b56f31a24458e866bee4623b5ce43
msgid "Using Gaussian Process to Model Competitor Offers"
msgstr "Uso de Procesos Gaussianos para Modelar Ofertas de Competidores"

#: ../source/notebooks/mmm/mmm_causal_identification.ipynb:580022
#: 373cd837f2ce4aec842b254d98f78922
msgid ""
"Since we do not directly observe competitor activities like offers or "
"discounts, we can treat ‘competitor_offers’ as a **hidden variable**. This "
"means we will not measure it directly but will infer its behavior based on "
"its impact on other variables in our model. A **Gaussian Process (GP)** can "
"help us model this hidden factor, as it is flexible enough to reflect the "
"data's underlying patterns."
msgstr ""
"Dado que no observamos directamente las actividades de los competidores, "
"como ofertas o descuentos, podemos tratar ‘competitor_offers’ como una "
"**variable oculta**. Esto significa que no la mediremos directamente, sino "
"que inferiremos su comportamiento en función de su impacto en otras "
"variables de nuestro modelo. Un **Proceso Gaussiano (GP)** puede ayudarnos a"
" modelar este factor oculto, ya que es lo suficientemente flexible para "
"reflejar los patrones subyacentes de los datos."

#: ../source/notebooks/mmm/mmm_causal_identification.ipynb:580024
#: da26d66267c4436cb6be71e7ef352fae
msgid "A Gaussian Process can be expressed as:"
msgstr "Un Proceso Gaussiano puede expresarse como:"

#: ../source/notebooks/mmm/mmm_causal_identification.ipynb:580026
#: 9aa5914978b043c5a383588da3991c52
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"\n"
"f(t) \\sim \\mathcal{GP}(m(t), k(t, t'))\n"
msgstr "f(t) \\sim \\mathcal{GP}(m(t), k(t, t'))"

#: ../source/notebooks/mmm/mmm_causal_identification.ipynb:580031
#: da3f7f3d958f4ea7ba5163f27ccd76fe
msgid ""
"$f(t)$: The hidden function representing ‘competitor_offers’ over time."
msgstr ""
"$f(t)$: La función oculta que representa ‘competitor_offers’ a lo largo del "
"tiempo."

#: ../source/notebooks/mmm/mmm_causal_identification.ipynb:580032
#: acf2f8ced4b3492bba3c80cd34e42d48
msgid ""
"$m(t)$: The mean function, often set to 0 unless we have prior knowledge of "
"a specific trend."
msgstr ""
"$m(t)$: La función media, a menudo establecida en 0 a menos que tengamos "
"conocimiento previo de una tendencia específica."

#: ../source/notebooks/mmm/mmm_causal_identification.ipynb:580033
#: c84e3dcf5e8c4cd4b21a27ee6d519b5b
msgid ""
"$k(t, t')$: The covariance function (or kernel), which determines the "
"smoothness and structure of $f(t)$."
msgstr ""
"$k(t, t')$: La función de covarianza (o núcleo), que determina la suavidad y"
" la estructura de $f(t)$."

#: ../source/notebooks/mmm/mmm_causal_identification.ipynb:580035
#: 9486be2ab11547db804b737bae6f9ba4
msgid ""
"PyMC-Marketing includes Gaussian Processes, using a **Hilbert Space Gaussian"
" Process (HSGP) approximation** to make calculations more manageable. This "
"allows us to approximate the hidden function $f(t)$ efficiently."
msgstr ""
"PyMC-Marketing incluye Procesos Gaussianos, utilizando una **aproximación de"
" Proceso Gaussiano en Espacio de Hilbert (HSGP)** para hacer que los "
"cálculos sean más manejables. Esto nos permite aproximar la función oculta "
"$f(t)$ de manera eficiente."

#: ../source/notebooks/mmm/mmm_causal_identification.ipynb:580037
#: 24489ea10ce24661a3fe6df397fd5ef4
msgid "Why Use a Gaussian Process?"
msgstr "¿Por qué utilizar un proceso gaussiano?"

#: ../source/notebooks/mmm/mmm_causal_identification.ipynb:580039
#: 3b1dded4a9924052909b9dcd99be0bc4
msgid ""
"Reveal the hidden structure of ‘competitor_offers’ and other unobserved "
"variables based on its connections to $x2$ and other observed variables."
msgstr ""
"Revele la estructura oculta de ‘competitor_offers’ y otras variables no "
"observadas basadas en sus conexiones con $x2$ y otras variables observadas."

#: ../source/notebooks/mmm/mmm_causal_identification.ipynb:580040
#: ade457887587499e99bcc013de59c24e
msgid ""
"Capture non-linear, varying effects that may arise from unseen competitor "
"activities."
msgstr ""
"Capture efectos no lineales y variables que pueden surgir de actividades de "
"competidores no visibles."

#: ../source/notebooks/mmm/mmm_causal_identification.ipynb:580042
#: 00b998b7549840debfd535f99fd8c908
msgid "Now let's see how we can implement this in PyMC-Marketing!"
msgstr "Ahora veamos cómo podemos implementar esto en PyMC-Marketing."

#: ../source/notebooks/mmm/mmm_causal_identification.ipynb:600002
#: ec9ef4b2a1a543c2bcbce0fd010753e8
msgid ""
"Let’s delve into the output. First, it’s important to note that our "
"adjustment set clearly indicates the need to control for both "
"**competitors** and **holidays** to accurately estimate our variables. This "
"implies that the variables in our regressions should include those factors "
"along with our treatment variables. Since we lack any observed variables in "
"the data to account for competitors, we set the parameter "
"`time_varying_intercept` to `True` so that our model can accommodate the "
"unobserved confounder."
msgstr ""
"Profundicemos en la salida. Primero, es importante señalar que nuestro "
"conjunto de ajustes indica claramente la necesidad de controlar tanto por "
"**competidores** como por **días festivos** para estimar con precisión "
"nuestras variables. Esto implica que las variables en nuestras regresiones "
"deben incluir esos factores junto con nuestras variables de tratamiento. "
"Dado que no contamos con ninguna variable observada en los datos para tener "
"en cuenta a los competidores, establecemos el parámetro "
"`time_varying_intercept` en `True` para que nuestro modelo pueda acomodar el"
" confusor no observado."

#: ../source/notebooks/mmm/mmm_causal_identification.ipynb:600004
#: 612cb42c57734bb398b96a2a97c744c4
